2999.Name: Mens Cleveland Clash
2999.Details:
Welcome to the Cleveland Clash!  How does it work?  Open to GCPTA/APTA members only.  Pick your partner just like a regular one day tournament.  The Clash will have a standard tournament bracket, but will run through the entire paddle season.  Teams are responsible for scheduling matches within a specified time frame.  

- 3 matches guaranteed
- Favor included
- Bring your own balls
- Standard three set matches and APTA rules govern play

Sign up now to fight for the ultimate title- Champion of the Land!
2999.WaiverText:
BY ALLOWING MY NAME TO APPEAR ON Cleveland Paddle, I and my partner agree to abide by all rules of Cleveland Paddle . I do hereby and on behalf of myself and my partner, heirs and legal representatives release and forever discharge Cleveland Paddle of and from any and all claims and demands of every kind, nature and character which I or my partner may have or may hereafter acquire for any and all damages, losses or injuries which may be suffered or sustained by me or my partner. I and my partner also understand that any special medical needs remain the responsibility of the individual player.
I and my partner hereby grant Cleveland Paddle permission to use our likeness in photograph(s)/video in any and all of its media, publications, whether now known or hereafter existing, controlled by Cleveland Paddle, in perpetuity, and for other use by Cleveland Paddle.  I and my partner will make no monetary or other claim against Cleveland Paddle for the use of such photograph(s)/video.

3516.Name: Cleveland Cup - Men's A
3516.Details:
This year’s Cup will feature a Men’s A Draw, a Men’s B Draw and a Women’s Draw.  The watch party for the semi-finals and finals will be held at The Country Club.  The host committee encourages you and your partner to register early in order to make sure you secure a spot and to facilitate planning for the event. If you are opting for a favor, please register BY FEBRUARY 14.  We anticipate it being a great event and look forward to seeing you on the courts! 

Winter Games Olympics Themed! 

2022 Cleveland Cup Host Committee
Julie Conrad, Adam Conrad, Tiffany Ottaway, and Matt Ottaway
